The Katsina state Governor, Aminu Bello Masari, has ordered the total locked down of the state capital effective Tuesday 21st April, 2020, following additional report of two persons who tested positive to COVID-19 in the state bringing a total to 12 with one death. He gave the order yesterday while briefing Journalists on the latest development on the pandemic in the state. He said, “From the break down, we now have two in Katsina, one in Dutsi-ma and the rest in Daura Local Government. “In line with what we have been doing since the outbreak of this disease, by way of locking down any city, town or Local Government, term have a confirmed case and we have discussed and agreed by 7, o’clock Tuesday morning there will be total stay at home in Katsina LGA entirely.” The Governor further disclosed by that the Tuesday date was chosen after considering that the state government must have paid April salary to workers before then. He called on the journalists and traditional rulers in the state assist Government in the fight to curb the spread of the virus in the state.